# CVE-2026-25681: html: escape greater-than symbol in doctype identifiers
#
# During HTML rendering, character references in DOCTYPE PUBLIC/SYSTEM
# identifier strings were not re-escaped, so a '>' character (decoded from
# &gt; during parsing) was written literally inside the quoted identifier.
# On re-parse this triggers an abrupt-doctype-system-identifier parse error
# that terminates the DOCTYPE early, allowing attacker-controlled bytes
# inside the identifier to escape into the data state. This may bypass HTML
# sanitizers built on golang.org/x/net/html.
#
# Renames writeQuoted -> writeDoctypeQuoted, adds a guard against mixed
# quote types in user-constructed Nodes, and HTML-escapes '>' in the
# rendered identifier. Also adds a regression test fixture that exercises
# the round-trip.
#
# Origin: upstream, https://github.com/golang/net/commit/4ece7b612ad44ad6c4d5e0d5d4df9c18cc211905
# Fixed-in: golang.org/x/net v0.55.0
# Affected: golang.org/x/net < v0.55.0 (target v0.39.0)

